JOHANNESBURG - Danny Jordaan is now the sole candidate for the position of South African Football Association (Safa) president. The other nominee, former PSL referee Ace Ncobo, has withdrawn from the presidential race set to be decided on 24 March. Ncobo as well as Chief Mwelo Nonkonyana had attempted to stop the election from taking place, citing governance concerns at Safa. But according to Fifa representative Phillip Chiyangwa, all matters have been resolved. READ: Safa presidential race gets interesting "We finally resolved all issues going forward and an agreement was executed,” Chiyangwa said. "I have had to deal with all the problems that have been raised by Ace and the other parties and I believe that other problems have been resolved. Safa is ready for elections," he added. eNCA